#+TITLE: Prelude to Riemannian geomeotry
#+SETUPFILE: ../res/mathsetup.org

* Riemannian manifold

#+ATTR_LATEX: :options [Hopf-Rinow]
#+BEGIN_theorem
#+LATEX: \label{thm:hopf-rinow}
<<thm:hopf-rinow>>
Given a Riemannian manifold $M$, the followings are equivalent
1. Every geodesic is well-defined at all time
2. Closed and bounded sets are compact.
#+END_theorem



